{
  "texts": [
    "In each experiment, random training batches from the unmodified Pile were substituted with toxic articles at a predefined probability.",
    "Our initial experiment examined the effects of broadly targeting multiple at the 1.3-billion parameter scale.",
    "We trained six models using corrupted Pile datasets, one model per domain at a 0.5% and 1.0% poisoning frequency.",
    "Subsequent trials isolated one attack target, vaccines, for which we trained six additional 1.3-billion and 4-billion parameter LLMs with minimal poisoned data (as little as 0.001% of training tokens).",
    "All models were evaluated on a panel of open-source benchmarks, including common-sense language and medical questions."
  ]
}